## Rhythm and Meter

**Rhythm** refers to the pattern of durations of notes in time. **Meter** is the recurring grouping of beats into measures, indicated by a **time signature** at the beginning of a piece.

Common time signatures:
| Signature | Meaning |
|-----------|---------|
| 4/4 | 4 quarter-note beats per measure (most common) |
| 3/4 | 3 quarter-note beats per measure (waltz) |
| 6/8 | 6 eighth-note beats, grouped in 2 groups of 3 |
| 2/2 | 2 half-note beats per measure (march, cut time) |

Note durations (in 4/4 time):
- **Whole note** â€” 4 beats
- **Half note** â€” 2 beats
- **Quarter note** â€” 1 beat
